!!
!! Control File for FSTR solver
!! Dynamic implicit analysis verifying ELEMENT-WISE (material) Rayleigh damping.
!!
!! Two geometrically identical but physically separate cantilever blocks are
!! loaded identically.  Global Rayleigh damping in !DYNAMIC is set to 0, so each
!! block's response is governed solely by its own !DAMPING (TYPE=RAYLEIGH):
!!   Block A (EA -> M1): lightly damped   (Rm=0.1, Rk=1.0e-3)
!!   Block B (EB -> M2): heavily damped   (Rm=3.0, Rk=5.0e-2)
!! Because the two blocks are otherwise identical, any difference in their
!! response confirms that the per-element damping coefficients are honored.
!!
!SOLUTION, TYPE=DYNAMIC
!STEP
!DYNAMIC
 1 , 1
 0.0, 4.0, 200, 0.02
 0.5, 0.25
 1, 1, 0.0, 0.0
 200, 1411, 200
 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1
!BOUNDARY
 FIX, 1, 3, 0.0
!CLOAD
 TIPA, 3, 0.1
 TIPB, 3, 0.1
!!
!! MATERIALS (element-wise Rayleigh damping)
!!
!MATERIAL, NAME=M1
!DAMPING, TYPE=RAYLEIGH
 0.1, 1.0e-3
!MATERIAL, NAME=M2
!DAMPING, TYPE=RAYLEIGH
 3.0, 5.0e-2
!!
!! SOLVER CONTROL
!!
!SOLVER,METHOD=CG,PRECOND=3,ITERLOG=NO,TIMELOG=NO
 10000, 1
 1.0e-8, 1.0, 0.0
!WRITE,RESULT,FREQUENCY=100
!OUTPUT_RES
ACC,ON
VEL,ON
!END
